**SplitEmBills:**

Main Idea:  
	An android app which will help in every day life by ***scanning paper bills*** and dividing them to many people.

	Why?  
		Have people ever went to a restaurant or supermarket, each of you buy your things by your side and when it’s time to pay, one person pay and then you *split the bill*?  
		That happens many times to me, so I figured I will make an app for it.  
	Purpose:  
		Basically: *Taking a paper bill (practically from anywhere), scan it through your phone and then divide the payments by items (depending on each others’ stuff).*  
	Problems:  
		How to read image data into computer readable stuff?  
		How to handle ‘splitting’ bills exactly?  
		How to make it simple and fun so that it’s easy to implement in real life?  
How to install:  
		Install it with the **.apk** binary on the root of the project

	Process:  
		**Main payer:**

- He will open the app; Signin (a simple ‘username’ authentication)  
- Choose to scan a bill; will be directed to a page opening his camera

  ![][image1]  ![][image2]

- Choosing to send the picture will bring him to a screen where he will have a **QrCode** (for the *co-payers* to join) and the **data the system was able to extract** out of the image.

  ![][image3]  ![][image4]


- He will get notified **in realtime** whenever someone join him in this payment.

				![][image5]

- Check on the items to ‘give to the other’ and assign it to them.

		![][image6]![][image7]

		**The “Co-payer”**

- Read the QrCode of the main payer.  
- Wait for assigned items to pop up on his side.

   ![][image8]  ![][image9]

- Proceed with his “**payment**”

  ![][image10]

Used technologies:

- flutter for the UI, the camera and qr libraries for accessing the mobile’s hardware  
- Golang for the little backend  
- Firebase for realtime in-app notification  
- Tesseract CLI for reading image text.
